{
  "texts": [
    "First, LLMs have limited context size and cannot be fed with entire databases (Pawar et al., 2024).",
    "Second, LLMs still struggle in processing structured data (Li et al., 2024a).",
    "Because of these issues, we adopt an agentic approach, where external tools (SQL scripts, in our case) are used by the LLM to handle structured data.",
    "While this is a popular solution, existing methods mostly produce \"shallow\" insights, such as the identification of simple trends or outliers (OpenAI, 2024a; LangChain, 2024b).",
    "As depicted in Figure 1, our idea is to obtain richer insights by first creating high-level questions over the database."
  ]
}